  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Undergoing lung resection surgery.

          -  18 years and older (without superior limit);

          -  Affiliated to french &quot;securité sociale&quot;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Emergency procedure

          -  litigation or search for compensation;

          -  Previous intervention in the same region;

          -  Peripheral neurological pathology (polyneuropathy) or central (brain damage, multiple
             sclerosis …) that may interfere with the evaluation of the post-operative pain

          -  Participation in another biomedical research protocol if there is an incompatibility
             with the present protocol.

          -  mental disability

          -  vulnerable person within the meaning of French law,

          -  poor understanding of French.
